As Sr. Avionics/Systems Engineering Analyst (Halifax)you will:
Performs technical planning, system integration, verification and validation, cost and risk and supportability and effectiveness analyses for total systems. Analyses are performed at all levels of total system product to include: concept, design, fabrication, test, installation, operation, maintenance and disposal. Ensures the logical and systematic conversion of customer or product requirements into total systems solutions that acknowledge technical, schedule and cost constraints. Performs functional analysis, timeline analysis, detail trade studies, requirements allocation and interface definition studies to translate customer requirements into hardware and software specifications.
Role will include support to the Canadian CP140 Aurora and other fleets, as well as other projects and support roles as may arise.
Responsible for implementing engineering projects and services that are specifically related to avionics systems (command, navigation, communication, antenna, power and electrical circuit) and electrical harnesses for military and commercial aircrafts.
Strong avionics technical experience expected.
Essential Functions:
Apply the aerospace industry knowledge for embedded systems (analog and digital) and the avionics software (i.e. define, design, develop, simulate, test, validate/verify);
Ensure adequacy between the established technical requirements and the proposed engineering solutions;
Ensure technical conformity of products and services in accordance to the internal and external customers needs;
Ensure the application of the internal processes and the policies of L3Harris MAS (engineering, materials and processes, airworthiness, project management, quality, etc.);
Apply the regulations, the standards, and aeronautical procedures (FAR, CAR, JAR, RAC, TAM, etc.) to support a certification package;
Participate in technical reviews and problems solving activities;
Prepare analyses and technical reports;
Analyze, design or modify schematic circuit and electrical cables;
Prepare or modify electrical drawings with computer-aided design and manufacturing (CAD-CAM) tool and/or computer aided design (CAD) tool in accordance to the company and customers standards;
Support the technical activities and the customer during prototypes realization.
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s Degree and minimum 6 years of prior relevant experience; or Graduate Degree and a minimum of 4 years of prior related experience.
Preferred Additional Skills:
Experience with FMS systems, autopilot systems, radar altimeter, IFF transponders, TCAS and NAV radios and aircraft intercommunication systems;
Aircraft optical sensor system experience with integration and ground/ flight test support;
Experience with airworthiness regulations in FAR23 or FAR25 type of aircraft, or equivalent DND experience.
Excellent written, oral, and presentation communication skills;
Experience working with subcontractors and Government customers;
Ability to work independently and in a team environment;
Hands-on experience with testing, integrating, and verifying hardware and/or software;
Experience developing, authoring, and implementing system test plans in a team environment;
Familiarity with ARINC 429, 1553, RS232/422, Ethernet, and other serial protocols.
Operational requirements:
Must be eligible for registration to the Controlled Goods Program;
Must be eligible to obtaining and maintaining the government of Canada’s “Reliability” status and Level 2 (Secret) security clearance;
